            From an early age I've been obsessed with user interfaces. I remember sketching a drag & drop idea on a napkin on a vacation to La Gomera, and rewatching the releases of the iPhone and iPad from my bed.
        </p>
        <p><strong>I am fascinated by the interaction between people’s minds and bodies and technology.</strong> Steve Jobs once made the comment that a computer is like a bicycle for the mind: it can make you think further with less effort. </p>
