        <p>
            <strong>I am a perfectionist.</strong> I like to perfect small, neat, intuitive things, and that sometimes means they turn out comically small. For the animation block at Minerva, some classmates made whole animated scenes. I made a ‘scroll down’ arrow gif of a few frames. I question every addition, and when a minor effect makes a website slow or too complicated, for example, I drop it.
        </p>
        <p><strong>A small creation reduced to essentials both inside and out is more satisfying to me than a larger but messier one</strong>, though I admire the latter and try to steal what I can. Writing explanations/tutorials helps me with this, as every unnecessary line of code/design element removed is one that I don’t have to explain. With code, I aim for snippets that are immediately grokkable (and, ideally, copy-pasteable).</p>
    </main>
